items.title: Piccadilly Circus
items.description:
Leonard Bentley posted a photo:

A multiview postcard showing two Vine Street Police Constables engaged on traffic duty sometime in the early 1960s. The officer on the left is at the junction of Shaftesbury Avenue and Piccadilly Circus, the officer on the right is standing beside the Underground entrance in Coventry Street just around the corner. For those gents who are old enough, which injector razor did you prefer PAL, Schick or Gillette?
items.author: nobody@flickr.com (Leonard Bentley)
